time complexity: O(high)
space complexity: O(high)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Dynamic programming is used to efficiently count the number of good strings by iteratively building up the count of strings of different lengths, utilizing the given zero and one values to transition between states, and accumulating the count within the specified range.
